92FS Vertec Inox: 
Specialized Combat Pistol
The Beretta 92FS Vertec Inox combines the benefits of the thinner vertical Vertec grip with some premium tactical and combat features found in other members of the 92 (M9) family. The sights are dovetail-mounted and easily replaceable by the user, the barrel is flush with the slide for a compact profile, and the Picatinny rail extending forward of the trigger guard makes this pistol ready for a variety of tactical accessories. In addition, the stainless steel finish makes the 92FS Vertec Inox particularly impervious to sweat, holster-wear, powder residues and corrosion, giving the user a virtual lifetime of trouble-free use.
Thin, Vertical Grip
The Vertec-style vertical grip of the 92FS Vertec Inox offers two very important benefits. Its vertical configuration makes it easy to point the handgun to where one would normally point the index finger of the dominant hand. This instinctive pointing is highly prized by tactical shooters and makes for consistent--and consistently-accurate--target acquisition. Also, the grips are thin in spite of being able to accommodate a double-stack, high-capacity magazine. This makes trigger-reach simple even for those with smaller hands, besides offering a more compact profile for those carrying this model concealed.
Dovetail-Mounted Sights, Easy Accessorization
Let’s face it: combat professionald and tactical-shooting aficionados often have strong personal preferences. This is why we consider it important to offer them not only several tactical-pistol variants that are ready to go out of the box, but also easy customization and accessorization options within a single model. Flush Cold-Hammer Forged Barrel for Superior Reliability
The cold-hammer forged barrel of the 92FS Vertec Inox is flush with the slide, which greatly minimizes the possiblity of it coming into contact with anything that may touch the crown. This, coupled with the inherent durability of every 92 model and the elegant ruggedness of the Inox (stainless steel) finish, makes the 92FS Vertec Inox a partner that will keep delivering accuracy and reliability for decades and tens of thousands of rounds

The HK Mark 23 Caliber .45 ACP pistol gives shooters match grade accuracy equal to that of the finest custom made handguns — yet exceeds the most stringent operational requirements ever demanded of a combat handgun. 

The Mark 23 provides this accuracy without the need for hand-fitted parts common in custom-built match pistols costing thousands of dollars more. 

One of the most thoroughly tested handguns in history, the MK23/Mark 23 project originated in 1991 when HK began development for the U.S. Special Operations Command, the organization that directs the activities of America's most elite military units, including the Navy SEALs and the Army Special Forces. 

On May 1, 1996, the first HK MK 23 pistols were delivered to the U.S. Special Operations Command for operational deployment, making the MK 23 the first caliber .45 ACP pistol to enter American military service since the venerable Government Model 1911A1. 

During testing, MK 23 pistols met the most stringent operational and accuracy requirements ever demanded of a combat handgun. Endurance testing demonstrated a service life of over 30,000 rounds of +P ammunition. To meet the reliability requirement, the pistol had to demonstrate a minimum of 2,000 mean rounds between stoppages (MRBS) with both M1911 ball and +P ammunition. All pistols exceeded the 2000 MRBS with an average of 6000 MRBS. In more than 450 accuracy test firings from a precision firing fixture at 25 meters, MK 23 pistols far exceeded the government requirement, averaging 1.44 inches, with 65 groups of less than one inch. postcontent:
I have a 2007 Yamaha FZ1-S for sale in Auburn. Text REDACTED for questions/to see the bike. No spam please. Details and Description below:

*Low insurance, Comfortable riding position, R1 engine with upgrades, Low miles
*Over $1,000 in high-end riding gear AND right at $1,500 in accessories/upgrades.

I bought this bike to be able to use motorcycle parking in Auburn for class during the summer semester. It do not drive it now so it is someone else's turn to enjoy it now for $6,300.00. This price includes a ton of extras and some very high quality accessories including Joe Rocket gear and a pair of matching Shoei helmets. I have the clean title and all it needs is a new owner. I just graduated as a teacher and need to sell the bike for family-oriented reasons. Bike was previously owned by a Jet Pilot for the US Air Force (very well taken care of and he is who did/had done all of the aftermarket stuff). I have taken good care of it as well with only Premium gasoline, high quality detailers, and non-aggressive driving. No track time or anything like that. Just a roll on the throttle every once in a while (because you just have to...). This bike has never been laid down or wrecked in any way. It cranks right up and will take you as long as you want to go very comfortably (more comfortable than my V star) and is really fast. It gets good gas mileage and has a digital gas gauge. The tires are in good shape (highest quality of tires you can buy Michelin Pilot)

INSURANCE ON THIS BIKE IS NOT EXPENSIVE. This is because it is considered a "Sports Touring" which means it is just as fast as a sports bike (or faster) and you do not have to lean uncomfortably or pay high insurance. You are basically buying a Yamaha R1 with aftermarket parts that is much more comfortable and cheaper to ride. The seating is similar to riding a dirtbike, but you can lean if you wish. Please don't ask silly questions like how fast does it go, I have no idea. I used it for parking about 4 miles from my home. I drove it 200 miles back from where I purchased it and that was the longest trip I have been on it, everything else has been in town. These bikes are meant to have a ton of miles on them and to be ridden for long distance thus accumulating a lot of miles. It is rare to find one of these without very high miles. This is your chance, this one has just under 13,700 (not even broken-in yet).

Kelly Blue Book has this motorcycle for cheaper than I am asking. KBB also does not allow you to adjust price for mileage and assumes by the year and the type of this bike that it has 40,000 miles on it. That should tell you something as far as how low the miles are. KBB also does not let you add on accessories on motorcycles or account for the gear it comes with. This bike is worth way more than what I am asking, especially considering what it comes with. SO please, don't waste my time with silly offers. Make a cash offer if you like, but I will probably keep all of the riding equipment that goes with the bike (over $1000 worth) unless it is very close to what I am asking. You may look online and this bike is priced right in there with those who have 20,000 miles and come with no aftermarket upgrades and no gear. This is a steal.

This bike has all the right accessories:
1. Two Brothers Racing Carbon Fiber Exhaust (great deep sound)
2. Tuned Gears to give it amazing mid-range power (this is not a beginner bike, Very Fast)
3. Zero-Gravity Windshield (you feel no air resistance)
4. Top Sellerie Gel Seat ($700 ordered from France, yes it is amazing)
5. Integrated Turn Signal Brake Lights (so you can remove the tag holder with blinkers)
6. K&N Intake & Filter
7. Ryder Clips Shift Sock (protects your shoes from shifting)
8. Spare Key (never been used)

It will also come with: (If you pay my asking price or we negotiate it in somehow)
1. (1) XL Shoei RF-800 Silver Helmet with new "light smoked" visor and a clear visor.
2. (1) L (matching) Shoei RF-800 Silver Helmet with clear visor.
3. Pair of XL Joe Rocket Riding Gloves
4. (1) XL Joe Rocket Atomic Motorcycle Jacket (with armor, like-new, very nice)
5. (1) XL Joe Rocket Riding Pants

Why I am selling:
I bought the bike to be able to park in Auburn easier than I would on my Yamaha V-Star 1100. I wanted a cool bike that was fun and comfortable ride and was light and easy to turn in downtown. My wife prefers to ride on the cruiser with me and I am now finished with college and have no time to ride, thus I do not need 2 motorcycles.

Grip panels are semi gloss finish American Walnut, with lower panel cut checkering and nickel plated Beretta Trident inlay Medallion. Slide is Government length, 1.15 inches thick, with rear lateral serrations, ambidextrous decocking safety levers, and internal firing pin safety. Extreme overall length is 8 5/8 inches from the muzzle to the grip frame strut. Grip frame is serrated fore and aft, 1.03 thick and tapering to .73 at the front of the frame. Trigger guard is type two serrated face. Weight empty is 33.8 ounces, about 40 ounces loaded, with center of gravity at the breech face. title: For Sale:  Lone Wolf threaded barrel/compensators,for Glock17
postcontent:
For sale is a (basically) new, threaded replacement barrel for the Glock 17, with a flash suppressor, as well as the Lone Wolf compensator.
The barrel alone sells for $125, the LW compensator sells for $60, and the flash suppressor sells for $20. After shipping, this would run around $200+.  I'll sell the entire set for $70,firm.
 Lone Wolf makes very popular,high-quality after-market Glock barrels, that can safely use plain lead bullets, unlike the factory barrel with the polygonal rifling. This barrel is also often used used to convert the .40 G22 to fire 9mm rounds. 
  Here's the info on the barrel from the manufacturer:
G17 9mm threaded 1/2 x 28 tpi
   Special features include: 
 -Ready to use, pre-fit drop in
 -No gunsmithing required
 -Precision machined from heat treated 416R stainless forgings, black oxide finish
 -Oversized lock-up area produces greater shot-to-shot accuracy 
 -Tighter dimensions than the original
 -Polished feed ramp and bore, diamond turned exterior 
 -Maximum chamber support, improved feed ramp design
 -Match grade broach cut rifling and target crown
 -Ok to use lead, plated or jacketed bullets
 Lifetime warranty

Here's the info on the compensator:
 "The Lone Wolf compensators offers a unique advantage to the discriminating competitive shooter. This exceptional performance is accomplished in 2 simultaneous steps. First, the redirection of gas to a 30 degree rearward angle actually pulls the barrel forward, reducing felt recoil. Second, the redirection of gas vertically provides a genuine reduction in muzzle rise. The result allows the shooters sights to remain on target or realigned quickly providing faster accurate follow up shots. Lone Wolf Distributors provides a quality engineered light weight system that delivers maximum performance at 1/2 the cost of similar compensators."

( I didn't have a photo of just the barrel and compensators, so I'm using this one, but this is an actual photo of them. BTW, this has been installed in a pistol, but is either un-fired, or had less than 10 rounds through it.)
